First approach is to see if we can make a prototype of the Git Bamboo Repository Plugin using the command line git executable first.

And then switch over to JGit.


question:
{quote}
4. Do you know if JGit supports SSH? If you do not, I believe its worth researching now as it may prevent us from using JGit in the future, and we should know about this soon.
{quote}

{quote}
approach to see if you can make a prototype of the Git Bamboo Repository Plugin using the command line git executable first.

And then switch over to JGit.

I think during the implementation of the prototype you should make it work on Unix (Mac and maybe Linux, if you are developing on Linux. If not, just support mac) and not worry about Windows for now. Also, do not worry about SSH support.

Only worry about all supported operating systems and SSH when you switch over to JGit.
{quote}

